  {
   "fieldname": "instruction",
   "fieldtype": "HTML",
   "label": "Instruction",
   "options": "<h5><b> Freezing Salary Assignment \u2013 Logic Overview</b></h5>\n  <p><strong>Reference Point:</strong> Payroll Date as defined in Stats Settings</p>\n\n  <b>1. Freezing Start Date Logic</b>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Start Date is <b>before</b> Payroll Date:  \n      Salary freeze begins from the <strong>same month</strong> as the Start Date.</li>\n    <li>Start Date is <b>after</b> Payroll Date:  \n      Salary freeze begins from the <strong>next month</strong>.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <b>2. Freezing End Date Logic</b>\n  <ul>\n    <li>End Date is <b>before</b> Payroll Date:  \n      Regular salary resumes from the <strong>same month</strong> as the End Date.</li>\n    <li>End Date is <b>after</b> Payroll Date:  \n      Regular salary resumes from the <strong>next month</strong>.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h5><b>Freezing End Type \u2013 Actions</b></h5>\n  <ul>\n    <li><b>Separation</b>:  \n      Manually create an <strong>Employee Resignation</strong> with the correct Freezing End Date.</li>\n    <li><b>Reactivation</b>:  \n      Regular salary resumes from the <strong>Freezing End Date</strong>.</li>\n    <li><b>Superior Reactivation</b>:  \n      Issue <strong>Additional Salary</strong> for the cut amount (in End Date month), then resume <strong>regular salary</strong> from the Freezing End Date.</li>\n  </ul>"
  },
